---

It was another exciting month for Tokyo Indies, featuring penguins, wizards, and friendly shiba inus. Read on to see what games we had!

[VRAM](https://maekawasdf.wixsite.com/vram) is a new event for game doujin of all types being held at Big Site on June 3.

!embed https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vfb-U9cxXd0
<iframe width="612" height="344" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/vfb-U9cxXd0?feature=oembed" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; encrypted-media" allowfullscreen></iframe>


[Orange](https://twitter.com/uvuofficial) discussed development of his clicker shmup [uVu - yoU Versus Universe](https://uvu.ambrella.co.jp/space/). 

!img tacticalbattle.jpg

[adachi_c](https://twitter.com/adachi_c) presented Tactical Battle, a tactics RPG [currently available](https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.ragegame.tacbattle2) on Android.

!embed https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gx4E_y5AfNQ
<iframe width="612" height="344" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/gx4E_y5AfNQ?feature=oembed" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; encrypted-media" allowfullscreen></iframe>


[Marco Llano](https://www.marcollano.com) gave a demo about creating interactive music and SFX for games.

!embed https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=SoNnujkU8k8
<iframe width="612" height="344" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/SoNnujkU8k8?feature=oembed" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; encrypted-media" allowfullscreen></iframe>


[Hojo Games](http://www.nishikinohojo.com/) showed off The Misanthropic Girl, a
3D action game for PC. A demo was just released this month and can be
downloaded [here](http://www.nishikinohojo.com/pages/1697864/Extra).

!img myex.gif

[New Deer](http://newdeer.net/) presented [My Exercise](https://www.myex.jp/), a game about an unusual fitness routine.

!embed https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=WBodSwXGRKw
<iframe width="612" height="344" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/WBodSwXGRKw?feature=oembed" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; encrypted-media" allowfullscreen></iframe>


[Tatsuya Uchida](https://twitter.com/_ukn_) showed off his mobile rhythm
game [PARADE!](https://twitter.com/parade_app) and dicussed its development and reception since release,
including his [top placement](https://developers-jp.googleblog.com/2018/04/3-indie-games-festival-2018.html)
at the recent [Google Indies Games Festival](https://gamefest.withgoogle.com/indie-game-fest).

That was it for this month - catch you next time! ðŸŽ®


